Description: Thirteen fragments of a papyrus roll, nine of which bear Coptic text on one or both sides. The four others are very small and bear no identifiable traces of writing. The fragments should be understood to be numbered in columns (top to bottom, left to right) as seen from the scanned image labelled as 'front'.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (380793) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/380793)
